Description: Foot of East Greek pottery closed vase, probably an oenochoe; micaceous pink-buff clay; outside differentially glazed; underside reserved with graffito 'A' and perhaps red dipinto.
Curator's comments: The walls were clearly quite thin, and so the piece was probably a jug rather than amphora.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.737)
